==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪki|-aɪki]]

===Interjection===
'''crikey!'''

#Used [[euphemistically]] for '''[[Christ]]''' as a mild expression of surprise, especially in Australia, and often in Britain. Made famous worldwide by Steve Irwin.
#Used as an exclamation, or as an emphasis of fact at the conclusion of a statement.
#: ''It's a hot day today, by '''crikey'''!''
#Often used with Moses, similar to crikey on its own, especially in Australia.
#: '''''Crikey''' moses!''
 
====Synonyms====
*[[criminy]], [[cripes]]

